						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">Maṇḍapa</hi> of Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>RAKSHASA.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the cyclic year Rākshasa, Vaiśākha, śu. 2 and may be corresponded to the 17th century.</p>						

						<p>Registers an agreement <hi rend="italic">(Yedureḍa)</hi> executed by Kōnapa, son of <hi rend="italic">Sthānāpati</hi> Anantarasa to Magatala Timmaya and other <hi rend="italic">reḍḍis</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Karaṇams</hi> of the village Prātakōṭa for 30 <hi rend="italic">varahās</hi> and remitted the <hi rend="italic">pulavari</hi> tax.</p>						

						</summary>
